tip.text: The carrot cake packs a punch - rich, but not too heavy, with just the right amount of sweetness. A lovely afternoon treat.
Delicious and homey Peranakan fare. The dishes aren't too spicy and definitely Nyonya-authentic. My fave is the ayam bua keluah. Sedap!

tip.text: This is homemade tiramisu and crumbly apple crumble. Love the texture and taste. Very homely!
Crunchy salad. Freshly picked greens! Love the summer colour.
Rosemary roast chicken. Very moist and tender. Love the juice!
Best calamari ever! This one's coated with a light, tangy batter. Some lemony perhaps? Love the springy texture and citrusy batter. Yummeh!!!
Seafood vongole. Huge amounts of yummy clams! Some spice added a kick to this dish too!
Ravioli with pesto sauce. Looks good and tastes yummy. Pesto sauce wasn't heavy and was a nice complement to the veggie-stuffed ravioli. Good size for the dumpling too.
This is Italian starters. You have eggplants, mushrooms, capsicums dipped in generous amounts of olive oil. Love the mushroom.
A really homely Italian restaurant. Food served fresh and taste like authentic Italian. We ordered the tasting menu and the food was delish! Love the cosy atmosphere too!

tip.text: Burger was toasty and the patty was juicy good. Truffle fries were yummy too!
This time, we tried the gnocchi potato with Parma ham, mascarpone pumpkin sauce and porcini. Looks simple, but the combination of taste was excellent!
The best lamb chops ever! Tender and super yummy.
Australian tenderloin with bearnaise sauce, similar to Hollandaise, magnificent pairing with the juicy meat. Thank goodness for this  at PS, otherwise have to settle for the fast food outlets here!
This is a shot of the amazing frothy, cream of mushroom soup. Yummeh!!
